<a name="5336"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">It’s Time to Fill Out Your CES Directory Listing!</div>
<br />

<IMG style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px" hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/2011_Directory_Cover.JPG" width=150 height=202>The <A href="http://ces12.mapyourshow.com/5_0/search.cfm?">MyCES Exhibitor Portal</A> is your gateway into the MyCES online directory as well as the printed Official International CES Show Directory.&nbsp;Hopefully you’ve already reviewed, updated and approved your information on the directory, but if you haven’t, you’ll want to be sure you’ve done so before the October 14 deadline.&nbsp; Any changes made after that date won’t make the printed directory but will still be displayed on the online floor plan.<BR><BR>You’ve already received an email from Map Your Show, our partners in producing both the online Directory and Official online Floor Plan (coming this fall).&nbsp;That email contained your user ID and password as well as a link to the <A href="https://ces12.exh.mapyourshow.com/5_0/login.cfm?">Exhibitor Dashboard</A>.&nbsp;If at any time you have any questions regarding the Online Exhibitor Directory, Floor Plan or Exhibitor Dashboard, you can email MYS at <A href="mailto:help@mapyourshow.com">help@mapyourshow.com</A> or give them a call at 888-527-8823.<BR><BR>***Please note that <A href="http://www.mapyourshow.com/" target=_blank>Map Your Show</A> is our only official vendor for MyCES and the directory. It has come to our attention that a company called <A href="http://www.fairguide.com/" target=_blank>FairGuide</A> is reaching out to our exhibitors to try to sell directory listing services. This company is in no way associated with CEA or the International CES.<br />
<img src="/images/framework/spacer.gif" width="1" height="20">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif" height="15" class="divider-line-long">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif" height="15" class="divider-line">
<br />
<a name="5335"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Exhibitor Registration is Now Open</div>
<br />

It's time to <A href="/exhibitors/register/default.asp">register your booth staff and top 10 buyers</A>. Register by December 7, 2011, to have your badges mailed to you.<BR><BR> Questions? Contact International CES Exhibitor Registration Customer Service at 866-233-7968 or <A href="mailto:exhreg@CE.org">exhreg@CE.org</A>.<BR><br />
<img src="/images/framework/spacer.gif" width="1" height="20">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif" height="15" class="divider-line-long">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif" height="15" class="divider-line">
<br />
<a name="5334"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Exporting Opportunities at CES </div>
<br />

<IMG style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px" hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/Globe1.jpg" width=200 height=200>Want to expand your global reach? With some 30,000 international attendees from 140 countries, CES is the place to find your next overseas business partner, distributor and investor. All CES exhibitors interested in exporting are encouraged to participate in our complimentary Exporting Exhibitor Program. Benefits include: 
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>Post-show list pull with contact information for attendees from up to 10 countries you select. </LI>
<LI class=text>Complimentary tickets to the international reception. </LI>
<LI class=text>Export counseling services provided by the U.S. Department of Commerce. </LI></UL>To participate in this program, indicate that you are interested in exporting opportunities when you update your <A href="/exhibitors/cesSmartBooth/default.asp">online directory listing</A>.<br />
<img src="/images/framework/spacer.gif" width="1" height="20">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif" height="15" class="divider-line-long">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif" height="15" class="divider-line">
<br />
<a name="5333"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Is Your Company Looking to Reach Consumers?</div>
<br />

<IMG style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px" hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/Tech_enthusiast.jpg" width=200 height=95>Partner with CEA in the Tech Enthusiast program – it’s free of charge and is a part of your CEA membership! This is a great opportunity to reach a tech-savvy audience interested in your newest products and services.&nbsp; Our corporate partners include other companies like Panasonic, Monster Cable and Newegg.&nbsp;<BR><BR>Your offer doesn’t have to be a discount – our Tech Enthusiasts also crave beta testing opportunities, pre-release information or videos displaying your products or services. We are also offering TE members a chance to win prizes through online contests. Providing products or services for the contests is a great way to get the word out to an influential audience. We understand partner offers may vary, so we can work with you to develop a flexible benefits package that suits your needs<BR><BR>Dozens of CES exhibitors have taken advantage of this opportunity to partner with CEA in the Tech Enthusiast program. Don’t miss out on this fantastic opportunity.&nbsp;&nbsp; To become a corporate partner – or to get more information about the program -- please contact Mary Savino at 703-907-7646 or <A href="mailto:msavino@ce.org">msavino@ce.org</A>.<br />
<img src="/images/framework/spacer.gif" width="1" height="20">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line-long.gif" height="15" class="divider-line-long">
<img src="/images/framework/divider-line.gif" height="15" class="divider-line">
<br />
<a name="5332"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Let The World Know!</div>
<br />

<IMG style="MARGIN-TOP: 0px; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px" hspace=5 align=right src="/images/content/2K12Innovations_SAMPLE.jpg" width=101 height=150>The <A href="/awards/default.asp">International CES® Innovations 2012 Design and Engineering Awards</A> is the most impressive and renowned awards program in the consumer technology industry. Being an Innovations Honoree can provide you with incredible opportunities, special recognition in the CE industry and worldwide exposure for your company and products.<BR><BR><STRONG>NEW for 2012</STRONG>: The Innovations product categories have been revamped, and we're introducing two brand <A href="/awards/innovations/categories.asp">new categories</A> — Software & Mobile Apps, and Tablets, E-Readers & Netbooks! We've also changed the online entry process, making the Innovations application quick, simple, and intuitive.<BR><BR>The <A href="/awards/innovations/cfe.asp">Call for Entries</A> opens on August 15, and you can save $200 by preparing your entry now and submitting before August 31.<BR><BR>Not <A href="/awards/innovations/about.asp">eligible to enter</A> this year? Sponsor the program to gain incredible exposure in the months leading up to CES and see your company featured among the most creative in the industry at the Innovations Showcase.<BR><BR>The <A href="http://cesweb.org/awards/innovations/callForJudges.asp">Innovations Call for Judges</A> is open now. If you're an independent designer, engineer or member of the press, we want you! Qualified exhibitors are eligible to judge categories in which their employers have not entered products. As a judge, you'll be the first to see the newest products in the CE industry. <A href="http://cesweb.org/awards/innovations/callForJudges.asp">Submit an application today</A>!
