<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" class="tableborder">
<tr>
    <td bgcolor="#1B3D85" class="columnsubhead"><div align="center">A Message From </div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
    <td>
    <p align="center"><img src="/images/content/Brandon_Moffitt.jpg" alt="Karen Chupka"><br>
    <span class="smallText">
    <strong>Brandon Moffitt</strong><br>
   Specialist, CES Administration</p>
    <hr align="center" width="90%" size="1" noshade color="#999999">
    <!-- article start -->
    <p><strong>Get Recognized at CES</strong><br> 
by Brandon Moffitt</p>
    <p><P>In today's technology industry, thousands of products and ideas compete for a highly coveted spot in not only a consumer's shopping cart, but in their lifestyle. With so many options to choose from, how does a consumer know which products deserve their hard-earned income? <BR><BR>Let CES give your product the edge consumers are looking for. By participating in a CES awards program, you can show consumers, the industry, and the world, what no marketing campaign is able to convey. Allow a panel of industry experts to analyze, evaluate, review, and critique your products and ideas, and show your potential customers what sets you apart from the rest. Whether you are a product designer or engineer, member of the press, or a maverick in the television and advanced media arena, CES has an award to recognize you.<BR><BR>Since 1976, the CES Innovations Design and Engineering Awards Program has recognized those products that stand as pillars of excellence in the consumer electronics industry. With entrants from 32 different product categories representing the hottest technologies in the world, the CES Innovations Awards have become the hallmark of the best-designed products in consumer technology. Everything from home theater speakers to digital imaging to in-vehicle technology will hold a place in the Innovations Awards program. The 2012 Innovations honorees will be announced at the New York Press Preview on November 8, 2011, at the Metropolitan Pavilion, and the award-winning products will be showcased at the 2012 International CES. The <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/awards/innovations/callForEntries.asp">Call For Entries</A> closes September 16, so make sure to visit and enter your product today. <BR><BR>CNET, the official live streaming and media partner for CES, will continue to produce the Best of CES Awards program for 2012. The CNET Best of CES awards name the most buzz-worthy, category-defining, innovative, and promising products at the show. The competition is judged by CNET’s esteemed editorial team, published online to their widespread audience, and includes the coveted Best of Show and People’s Voice awards. No submission is necessary - but make sure CNET editors know what you'll be debuting at CES. <A href="http://www.cnet.com/2723-13403_1-461-8.html">Pitch your products now</A>!<BR><BR>The International Academy of Web Television (IAWTV) is holding its inaugural IAWTV Awards at the 2012 International CES. The IAWTV Awards is the first award show within the web television industry to be presented by content creators, for content creators and will allow members of the IAWTV to honor the best of their profession, while networking among industry luminaries. Proceeds raised from the show are to be used for the betterment of the community by providing more member resources as well as professional development and education for web television professionals. With online audiences for web television reaching millions, the IAWTV Awards is expecting event coverage the world over. For more information about the IAWTV and awards sponsorship opportunities, please visit <A href="http://www.iawtv.org">www.iawtv.org</A>.<BR><BR>Lastly, since 1948, the National Academy of Televisions Arts & Sciences has hosted the Emmy Awards for Outstanding Achievement in Engineering and Technical Development.&nbsp; This will be the fifth consecutive year that the awards will be presented during the International CES.&nbsp; This awards program recognizes companies, individuals or scientific/technical organizations for advances in engineering technologies that improve reception, recording or transmission of television programming.&nbsp; The awards are presented at a special ceremony during the 2012 International CES.&nbsp; What a way to enhance your show experience! Please visit <A href="http://emmyonline.tv/tech/">http://emmyonline.tv/tech/</A> for more information on the awards.<BR><BR>Awards programs at CES are just one more way help your company stand out at the most important consumer technology event of the year. Go for the gold and start building your brand today!<BR><BR>Sincerely,<BR><BR>Brandon Moffitt</P></p>
    <!-- article end -->
    </span>
